  • Field Details

    • IDENTITY

      public static final Complex IDENTITY
      The identity number. This is the real number equivalent of 1.

    • I

      public static final Complex I
      The square root of -1.

      Multiplying a complex number by i will rotate the number 90 degrees counter-clockwise along the real-complex number plane.

    • equals

      public boolean equals(@Nullable Object obj)
      Checks for equality between this number and the provided object obj.

      This method respects the mathematical concept of complex numbers, and only treats complex numbers which have the same components as equal.

      Scalar values (real numbers) of the same representation will not be considered equal.

      Specified by:
      equals in interface Vector<Double,Double2>
      Overrides:
      equals in class Double2
      Parameters:
      obj - The object to compare to
      Returns:
      true if the other object is also a complex number, and both the real and imaginary parts are equal

    • looseEquals

      public boolean looseEquals(@Nullable Object obj)
      Checks for loose equality between this number and the provided object obj.

      This method will return true if either the other object is a Number and the value it represents is equal to that of this complex number's value, or if the other object is equal to this number in the context of Double2.equals(Object).

      If the imaginary part (the Y component) of this number is exactly zero, it will allow comparison with real numbers.

      If the other object is not an instance of Number, it will follow the equality logic of Double2.equals(Object).

      Parameters:
      obj - The object to compare to
      Returns:
      true if the object is considered equal to this number as the description above
